Advanced Java Example

  The {{{${gh-url}/examples/java/src/main/java/org/openpcf/neo4vertx/examples/AdvancedDemoVerticle.java}AdvancedDemoVerticle}} example shows how to access the neo4j graph database directly though java without using the event bus. It is possible to get the neo4j graph database service by calling <<<Neo4jGraphVerticle.getDatabase()>>>.

  The runnable contains a simple request handler that will add a dummy node to the neo4j graph.  

